Join Node: Add Related Columns of Data to the Recipe
Use a Join Node in the Recipe Canvas

In CRM Analytics, create joins between Salesforce objects, external objects, and CRM Analytics datasets in a recipe.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
To manage and create a recipe: Edit CRM Analytics Dataflows OR Edit Dataset Recipes

To use a Join Node:
Select Add Node button from a single node or between two nodes.
Select Join.
Choose the data to join and columns to include.
Click Next.
Choose the join type.
Change the join keys if needed.
Use multiple keys to match records.
Don't use CRM Analytics datasets date and time component fields as join keys.

To add a prefix for columns coming from the right data source, enter a prefix.
Select Lookup Multiple Values for the lookup to return all matching rows.
In the Columns tab, select the columns to include in the recipe.
Click Preview to show joined columns and their data.
Hide or show columns as needed.
Click Apply to add the node to the recipe.
Save the recipe.
